(12433, 764, '_tax_rewards_for_multi-family_developers_heading', 'field_61adb8327e70f'),
(12434, 764, 'tax_rewards_for_multi-family_developers_content', '<h5>A Federal Tax Credit Worth $2,000 Per Qualifying Unit</h5>\r\n<p>The 45L Federal tax credit is designed to encourage the construction of energy-efficient dwellings, and has been available to eligible contractors since 2006. However, this energy-efficient incentive is still under-publicized, and thus, under-utilized.  </p>\r\n<p>Section 45L provides an income tax credit to homebuilders and multifamily residential developers to encourage them to invest in building energy-efficient properties.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Eligible Properties:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Affordable housing (LIHTC)</li>\r\n	<li>Apartment properties - up to 3 stories </li>\r\n	<li>Single family homes</li>\r\n	<li>Assisted living housing</li>\r\n	<li>Student housing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Multifamily residential properties four or more stories above grade could qualify under section <a href=\"#\">179D deduction</a></p>'),
(12435, 764, '_tax_rewards_for_multi-family_developers_content', 'field_61adb8407e710'),
(12436, 764, 'how_it_works_title', 'HOW?'),
(12437, 764, '_how_it_works_title', 'field_61adb881e1bb8'),
(12438, 764, 'how_it_works_content', '<p>Each unit should provide a level of energy efficiency higher than national energy standards, however, many of the newer developments already exceed these standards based on recent building codes. We recommend that any apartment or condominium project (new construction or rehabilitation) within the past four years be evaluated for the 45L tax credit.  </p>\r\n<p>Properties must be three stories or lower and incorporate energy-efficient features such as high R-value insulation and roofing, windows, doors, and/or HVAC systems.</p>\r\n<a href=\"#\">Get Started</a>'),
