inancialsolutions/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/value1.png\" alt=\"\" /> Partnership</h3>\r\n<p>Collaboration for mutual benefit with our clients and within is fundamental to delivering lasting performance through mutual growth.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" el_id=\"principle-block\" el_class=\"custom_inner_content\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text]</p>\r\n<h2>3 Key Principles of Our Win-Win Approach</h2>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"box\" width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"22\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]We’re a dynamic organization that values and rewards ideas.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"box\" width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"24\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]We foster a culture of flexibility with an emphasis on results and collaboration.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"box\" width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"23\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]Our partnerships are based on mutual trust and sharing of fundamental values.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\"join-team\"]<a href=\"#\">Join our team</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" el_id=\"top_partner\"][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" el_id=\"custom-testimonials\" el_class=\"custom_inner_content\" css=\".vc_custom_1633441878561{background-image: url(http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/testibg.png?id=41) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_raw_html]JTVCdGVzdGltb25pYWxfc2hvcnRjb2RlJTVE[/vc_raw_html][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>\r\n', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-11-24 05:45:12', '2021-11-24 05:45:12', '', 8, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?p=783', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(784, 1, '2021-11-24 07:16:18', '2021-11-24 07:16:18', '<h3>$50M acquisition of 400,000 square foot office building with first floor retail in Colorado</h3>\r\nMeridian was retained to perform a detailed engineering-based cost segregation study for depreciation / fixed asset purposes on the purchase of a 400,000 square foot $50 million dollar office building in Colorado.Our study resulted in net present value cash flows over the life of the investment of $2.1 million and an Increase in first year cash flow by $1.2 million.\r\n\r\nOur studies provide internal accounting with complete component unit cost detail for the entire building, giving the CPA the ability to retire assets. Additionally we customized the building detail based on our client’s long-term vision for the property. This study was broken out by tenant, suiteand asset class to make it easy to identify changes to the building.\r\n\r\nAs the building changes overtime, we serve as a resource to help internal accounting maximize the value of partial dispositions. Our methodology takes the burden of proof off the taxpayer and the CPA,and clearly delineates the “what, why &amp; how” we claim as personal property versus real property for the entire building in a construction format easy for the IRS to follow under audit. A clear, easy- to-follow documentation trail is very important to minimize time under audit.\r\n\r\nTwo years later, the building owners re-leased a first floor retail tenant’s space to a restaurant group. The HVAC for the space was a single zone RTU with ductwork above the acoustical ceiling.\r\n\r\nThe reconfiguration for the restaurant, open ceiling style, required changing the layout and ductwork materials, providing an opportunity to retire the remaining basis in the original retail ductwork. The details in the original Meridian study are easily identifiable, so the partial disposition can be maximized resulting in an additional $261K tax write-off.\r\n\r\nThis was one of several opportunities in the restaurant space. In year three, there were roof repairs as well as two office tenant changes requiringbasic upgrades to the lighting, kitchen, and plumbing.The same level of detail was applied to the build-outs based on contributions by both the landlord and tenant,enabling the building owner to maximize both depreciation and retirements for the life of the property. In Just Three Years, Total Disposition Write Offs For This Client Were $1.4M.', '$2.1M in1st year cash flow and $1.2M in dispositionsover next 3 years.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-1m-in1st-year-cash-flow-and-1-2m-in-dispositionsover-next-3-years', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:25:24', '2021-12-03 17:25:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=784', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(785, 1, '2021-11-24 07:39:10', '2021-11-24 07:39:10', '<h3>13 story mixed-use property with a cost basis of $110 Million - excluding land</h3>\r\nMeridian was engaged to perform a Purchase Price Allocation and Fixed Asset Study on the acquisition and phased improvementsof a multi-tenant office building with first floor retail and a three story parking garage. The purpose of the study was to create a basis to properly value and componentize the capitalized costs enabling the taxpayer to maximize the value of future retirements.\r\n\r\nThe CPA directed the assets to be classified according to the Alternative Depreciation System (ADS) due to the new interest expense limitations outlined in the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act (TCJA). The office building required $8.5 million in improvements to include the initial building refresh and, in 2019, a 60% tenant contribution for the build-out of a restaurant to replace the bank previously occupying a portion of the first floor.\r\n\r\nPotential long-term plans include developing the complex into a work/live/play atmosphere by bringing in a large co-working space tenant, personal training gym, and other convenience-based tenants. Future phases may also include four floors of multi-family atop the adjoining parking garage. Over the next two to seven years, a complete interior and exterior overhaul is expected to occur in phases.\r\n\r\nMeridian’s engineering methodology re-estimated the project in a valuation method the IRS accepts with an emphasis on details for both short and long life assets for ADS. Our methodology is consistent with construction estimating techniques that use the latest disposition/maintenance &amp; repair rules, Unit of Property (UOP) concept, and the recent Capitalization of Tangible Property Regulations. The detail and documentation trail are set up to facilitate the retirement of assets associated with the original retail space, as well as the additional structural building components that will need to change to accommodate the new restaurant build-out and building refresh.\r\n\r\nThe study was organized by tenant, suite, asset class and building use to enable internal accounting to easily maximize the value of future retirements associated with renovations and demolition driven by tenant changes, expansion, and building upgrades.', 'Purchase Price Allocationon $110MM acquisition with ADS  Election.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'purchase-price-allocationon-110mm-acquisition-with-ads-election', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:26:39', '2021-12-03 17:26:39', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=785', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(786, 1, '2021-11-24 07:43:50', '2021-11-24 07:43:50', '<h3>New Construction of $25MMMulti-Family Community in Arizona</h3>\r\nMeridian wasreferred to perform a cost segregation analysis for the new construction of a residential rental complex in Arizona. The investment totaled more than $25 million exclusive of land value.\r\n<h4>Engineering Process</h4>\r\nMeridian’s experienced professionals applied their knowledge of engineering, construction, and architectural design, along with a thorough understanding of the IRS depreciation guidelines, to complete a cost segregation analysis of the property the same tax year it was capitalized. Our professionals completed an extensive site inspection and reviewed comprehensive property documentation. The deliverable report included detailed documentation and calculations for each asset and cited tax law to support all asset classifications.\r\n<h4>Study Results</h4>\r\nReclassification of assets resulting from our study yielded $4.5 million of land improvement property with a fifteen-year life and $4.75 million of personal property with a five-year life. The client met the requirements for 100% bonus depreciation resulting in approximately $9.8 million in depreciation and a $3.9 million dollar cash benefit in year one.', '$3.9 million dollar cash benefit in year one', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-9-million-dollar-cash-benefit-in-year-one', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:27:10', '2021-12-03 17:27:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=786', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(787, 1, '2021-11-24 07:54:45', '2021-11-24 07:54:45', '<h4>New Construction of Assisted Living Facility in Georgia</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by a national assisted living provider to conduct an Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study for a new assisted living residence.  The objective was to identity property components that could be reclassified to shorter recovery periods to accelerate building depreciation and defer income taxes. In addition, the frequent resident turnover and constant state of repairs provide the opportunity to help increase the benefit recognized by the taxpayer by accounting for repair expenses and partial dispositions.\r\n<h4>Tax Benefits Summary</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cost Basis: $3,200,000</li>\r\n<li>Cost Reallocated: $1,151,000</li>\r\n<li>Reallocation Percent: 36%</li>\r\n<li>1st Year Cashflow : $283,221</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Engineering Process</h4>\r\nOur construction engineers performed a complete analysis of all available construction drawings and specifications, contractor payment applications, invoices, and other supporting documentation. We prepared a detailed analysis of all accumulated data on a property unit basis for cost allocation purposes under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code. We then performed an on-site inspection to verify, photograph, and document the property. Finally, our internal audit team of senior construction engineers and tax specialists reviewed and certified completeness and accuracy.\r\n<h4>Project Results</h4>\r\nThe client reallocated $1,151,000 or 36%of the assets to shorter recovery. First-year depreciation is projected to be a total of $708,053.', 'First year projected increased cashflow of $283,221', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'first-year-projected-increased-cashflow-of-283221', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:28:01', '2021-12-03 17:28:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=787', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(788, 1, '2021-11-24 07:57:56', '2021-11-24 07:57:56', '<h4>Acquisition of a warehouse/office building in Utah</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by the owners of a food distributor to conduct an Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study for a recently purchased $2.5 million dollar single story warehouse and office building. The Study objective was to identity property components that could be reclassified to shorter recovery periods to accelerate building depreciation and defer income taxes. \r\n<h4>Property Profile</h4>\r\nThe property is a single story combination warehouse and office building containing approximately 74,911 square feet. The building is a steel-framed structure enclosed with EIFS  and metal panels, and insulated glass in metal frames. Land improvements included sidewalks, paved parking lot, flagpole, double swing gate, site signage, underground utilities, and general landscaping with irrigation.\r\n<h4>Engineering Process</h4>\r\nOur construction engineers conducted a detailed inspection and itemized the improvements located on this purchased property. We reviewed all available construction documentation, and along with the inspection information we isolated various components qualifying for shorter cost recovery period depreciation under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code and current tax law. Using construction-estimating techniques, each component is assigned a value, which is adjusted for depreciation and reconciled back to the purchase price. Finally, our internal audit team of senior construction engineers and tax specialists reviewed and certified its completeness and accuracy.\r\n<h4>Project Results</h4>\r\nAs a result, of this Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study the client reallocated 35%of the assets to shorter recovery.  This generated a first year depreciation of roughly $900,938, and a year- one projected net present valuetax benefit of $307,852', 'First year depreciation of $900,938 and $307,852 NPV tax benefit', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'first-year-depreciation-of-900938-and-307852-npv-tax-benefit', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:28:34', '2021-12-03 17:28:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=788', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(789, 1, '2021-11-24 07:59:55', '2021-11-24 07:59:55', '<h4>22 Auto Dealerships in the Northeast</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by an auto-dealer who initially indicated they were already performing cost segregation.  Per the request of their new CPA, Meridian performed a comprehensive analysis of 22 dealerships with a total cost basis of roughly $55 million.\r\nEven though, all of the dealerships had already completed a cost segregation study, Meridian identified an additional 18% of accelerated depreciation on top of what the prior cost segregation provider had previously identified, resulting in an addition $3.5 million in increased cash flow.\r\nAdditionally, the component cost detail provided in our cost segregation study shows detailed component costs for both personal and real property – providing the ability to easily retire assets during future remodeling, repairs or demolition.  Meridian’s work helped the new CPA show his value to the client.', 'We uncovered18% more depreciationafter theclient completeda study', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'we-uncovered18-more-depreciationafter-theclient-completeda-study', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:29:04', '2021-12-03 17:29:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=789', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(790, 1, '2021-11-24 08:00:56', '2021-11-24 08:00:56', '<h4>Light Manufacturing Distribution Facility in North Carolina</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged to perform a Cost Segregation study on a $19.2 million distribution facility in North Carolina.  Roughly $1.2 million in FF&E and easily identifiable short life assets were already accounted for on the depreciation schedule.  This left $18 million locked in the 39 year building category.\r\nOur construction engineers performed a complete analysis of all available construction drawings and specifications, contractor payment applications, invoices, and other supporting documentation. We prepared a \r\ndetailed analysis of all accumulated data on a property unit basis for cost allocation purposes under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code. We then performed an on-site inspection of the 185,000 square foot facility to verify, photograph, and document the property. Finally, our internal audit team of senior construction engineers and tax specialists reviewed and certified its completeness and accuracy. \r\nBased on the detailed site visit and subsequent calculations using construction plans and invoices, Meridian was able to successfully reclassify  just over $6.5 million, or 36%  percent of the construction costs into 5 and 15 year property. This generated an increased first year cash flow in excess of $1.6 million.\r\n', 'Increased1styear cash flow by $1.6M after client completed a study', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'increased1styear-cash-flow-by-1-6m-after-client-completed-a-study', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:29:49', '2021-12-03 17:29:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=790', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(792, 1, '2021-11-24 08:07:05', '2021-11-24 08:07:05', '<h4>Fast Food Restaurant in Ohio</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by the owners of a franchise restaurant in the Midwest to conduct an engineering-based Cost Segregation Study for a recently purchased single-story building located in a popular suburban retail location. The was to identity property components that could be reclassified to shorter recovery periods to accelerate building depreciation and defer income taxes. The property is a single-story building with a size of approximately 7,300 square feet. The property has a cost basis of $3,000,000 and was acquired and placed into service in 2019.\r\n<h4>Property Specifications</h4>\r\nThe building exterior walls are concrete blocks finished with brick veneer. The windows are insulated fixed glass in aluminum frames. Interior finishes include drywall over metal stud partitions finished with paint, vinyl wall covering, marlite and stainless steel wall protection, and hollow metal and wood doors with frames and hardware. There is a year-round heating, ventilation, and air-conditioning system provided by gas and electric rooftop units. The kitchen equipment includes exhaust hoods, fans, and a make-up air system. Electrical systems include power distribution equipment, fluorescent and incandescent light fixtures, receptacles, switches, conduits, and wires. There are multiple kitchen equipment electrical hook-ups. Land improvements include asphalt paving, concrete sidewalks, concrete curbing, concrete dumpster pad, dumpster enclosures, and landscaping with irrigation.\r\n<h4>Methodology</h4>\r\nOur construction engineers conducted a detailed inspection and itemized the improvements located on this purchased property. We reviewed all available construction documentation, and along with the inspection information, we isolated the various components qualifying for shorter cost recovery period depreciation under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code and current tax law. \r\nAs a result, the client was able to reallocate $1.56 million or 52% of the assets to a shorter recovery. The client has since engaged Meridian to review their entire nationwide portfolio as the incremental value provided by Meridian’s expert guidance made a substantial impact to their overall tax planning.\r\n', '52% of assets reallocated to a shorter recovery period', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-of-assets-reallocated-to-a-shorter-recovery-period', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:30:29', '2021-12-03 17:30:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=792', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(793, 1, '2021-11-24 08:26:26', '2021-11-24 08:26:26', '<h4>New Acquisition of Dental Clinic</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by a group of dentists serving a suburban community in the Northwest to conduct an Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study for a recently acquired single story dental \r\noffice facility.\r\n<h4>Tax Benefits Summary</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cost Basis: $1,490,095 </li>\r\n<li>Cost Reallocated: $679,483 </li>\r\n<li>Reallocation Percent: 46% </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Project Results</h4>\r\nAs a result of this Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study the client reallocated$ 679,483or 46%of the assets to a shorter recovery, and the client’s first year adjusted cash flow is expected to be $282,430.', 'First year tax benefit of $282,430 and 46% of assets reallocated', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'first-year-tax-benefit-of-282430-and-46-of-assets-reallocated', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:30:57', '2021-12-03 17:30:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=793', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(794, 1, '2021-11-24 08:32:02', '2021-11-24 08:32:02', '<h3>$6.2M expansion to accommodate tenant changes for a 20-year-oldretail plaza</h3>\r\nThe owners of a grocery/retail shopping center hired Meridian to conduct a cost segregation analysis on the improvements, renovation, and expansion of an an80,000 square foot retail plaza the client acquired 20 years earlier.\r\nThe $6.2 million renovations included the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Conversion of the grocery store tenant spaces into four white box spaces</li>\r\n<li>Tenant allowances for the suites</li>\r\n<li>Ground-up construction of a 4,600 square foot shell building</li>\r\n<li>Tenant allowance for a new restaurant chain store</li>\r\n<li>Improvements to the entire site infrastructure</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Engineering Process </h4>\r\nOur construction engineers performed a complete analysis of all available construction drawings and specifications, contractor payment applications, invoices, and other supporting documentation for the original purchase and current renovation. We prepared a detailed analysis of all accumulated data on a property unit basis for cost allocation purposes under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code. We then performed an onsite inspection to verify, photograph, and document the property. Finally, our internal audit team of senior construction engineers and tax specialists reviewed and certified its completeness and accuracy. \r\n<h4>Study Results</h4>\r\nOur work resulted in first-year depreciation of $3.4 million and a $1.4 million increase to first-year cash flow.  Plus, we identified $1.3 million in dispositions, allowing the client to reduce the remaining basis on the original purchase. This acceleration in depreciation allows property investors to reduce their tax liability.  Additionally, by breaking down the building asset into components, our cost segregation methodology allows our clients to easily identify future benefits of abandonment, repairs, routine maintenance, and overall asset management as tenants change over the life of the asset.', '$3.4M in 1st Year Depreciation and $1.3M in dispositions on renovations', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-4m-in-1st-year-depreciation-and-1-3m-in-dispositions-on-renovations', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:31:30', '2021-12-03 17:31:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=794', 0, 'studies', '', 0),
(795, 1, '2021-11-24 08:34:17', '2021-11-24 08:34:17', '<h4>Leasehold Improvements for Build-Out of Surgery Center in Florida</h4>\r\nMeridian was engaged by a medical practice to conduct a cost segregation analysis on $1.7 million in leasehold improvements for the build-out of a surgery center. The objective was to identity property components that could be reclassified to shorter recovery periods to accelerate building depreciation and defer income taxes.\r\n\r\nOur construction engineers performed a complete analysis of all available construction drawings and\r\nspecifications, contractor payment applications, invoices, and other supporting documentation. We prepared a\r\ndetailed analysis of all accumulated data on a property unit basis for cost allocation purposes under the\r\nprovisions of the Internal Revenue Code. We then performed an on-site inspection to verify, photograph, and\r\ndocument the property. Finally, our internal audit team of senior construction engineers and tax specialists\r\nreviewed and certified its completeness and accuracy.\r\n<h4>Project Results</h4>\r\nAs a result of this Engineering-based Cost Segregation Study, the client was able to reallocate 67% of assets or $1,139,000 to a shorter 5-year life equating to first-year cash benefits of $461,354.', '67% of assets reallocated to shorter life resulting in $461,354cash benefit in year one', 'Meridianwas engaged by a medical practice to conduct a cost segregation analysis on $1.7 million in leasehold improvements for the build-out of a surgery center.  The objectivewas to identity property components that could be reclassified to shorter recovery periods to accelerate building depreciation and defer income taxes. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '67-of-assets-reallocated-to-shorter-life-resulting-in-461354cash-benefit-in-year-one', '', '', '2021-12-03 17:32:01', '2021-12-03 17:32:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost/meridianfinancialsolutions/?post_type=studies&#038;p=795', 0, 'studies', '